In a mixing bowl, beat brown sugar, oil, egg and vanilla until smooth. Combine flour, salt and baking soda; add to sugar mixture alternately with milk. Beat until smooth. Stir in rhubarb and almonds. Pour into two greased 9-in. round cake pans. For topping, combine sugar and butter; stir in almonds. Sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350 degrees F for 30-35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near the center comes out clean.